Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, low total COâ‚‚, and significant proteinuria, suggesting possible renal impairment with metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal, high protein, glucose, and ketones) further support renal dysfunction and possible glycosuria/ketonuria, despite low HbA1c and normal serum glucose. No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease.
